Preheat the oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle over some @oil{} and season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss the potatoes well to evenly coat in the oil and seasoning. Arrange in a single layer on the tray. Pop on the top shelf to roast until crisp and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}, turning halfway through.

Carefully wrap each @British hickory smoked sausages{2} 'top to toe' in two rashers of @British streaky bacon{4}. Place them on another baking tray with a little @oil{} drizzled on top. Pop the sausages on the middle shelf of the oven. Roast for ~{20-25%minutes}, until the bacon is golden and the sausage cooked though. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: The hotdog needs to be cooked all the way through.

Half, peel and finely slice the @onion{1}. Heat a good splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-low heat. Once hot, add the onions and a large pinch of @salt{}. Cook until very soft and starting to colour, ~{15%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> TIP: If it looks like they're starting to burn, add a splash of water! When golden, stir in the @sugar{1/2%tsp} until melted, then remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, trim the @cucumber{1/2} and slice into thin circles. Pop the @sugar for the pickle{1/2%tsp} and the @white wine vinegar{6%tbsp} into a #small bowl{}. Stir to dissolve the sugar. Add the sliced cucumber. Gently toss to coat and set aside. Halve the @green chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed then finely chop. Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%can} in a #sieve{}.

Transfer half the onions into a small bowl. Set aside. Stir the mixed beans, @tomato passata{1%can} and half the @chipotle ketchup{1/2} into the pan that has the remaining onions in. Return to medium-high heat and fry until reduced, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When there are 5 mins left on the sausages, cut open your @brioche hot dog buns{2} by slicing two thirds of the way through the centre. Pop on the middle shelf of the oven to toast, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once everything is cooked, spread the rest of the @chipotle ketchup{} onto the rolls, then put a sausage into each. TWIST IT UP: Squeeze in a few slices of the pickled cucumber and spoon the sticky onions over the top! Add some @soured cream{150%g} and a sprinkle of @?chilli{} (for those who would like). Serve on plates with the wedges and bonfire beans on the side. Enjoy!